ull]] is killed on [[Standing Rock Indian Reservation]], leading to the [[Wounded Knee Massacre]]. *[[1905]] &ndash; The [[Pushkin House]] is established in [[Saint Petersburg]], Russia, to preserve the cultural heritage of [[Alexander Pushkin]]. *[[1906]] &ndash; The [[London Underground]]'s [[Great Northern, Piccadilly and Brompton Railway]] opens. *[[1914]] &ndash; World War I: The [[Serbian Army]] recaptures [[Belgrade]] from the invading [[Austro-Hungarian Army]]. * 1914 &ndash; [[List of accidents and disasters by death toll#Industrial disasters|A gas explosion]] at [[Mitsubishi]] Hōjō coal mine, in [[Kyushu]], Japan, kills 687. *[[1917]] &ndash; World War I: An [[armistice between Russia and the Central Powers]] is signed. *[[1933]] &ndash; The [[Twenty-first Amendment to the United States Constitution]] officially becomes effective, repealing the [[Eighteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|Eighteenth Amendment]] that [[Prohibition in the United States|prohibited]] the sale, manufacture, and transportation of [[Alcoholic beverage|alcohol]]. *[[1939]] &ndash; ''[[Gone with the Wind (film)|Gone with the Wind]]'' (highest inflation adjusted grossing film) receives its premiere at [[Loew's Grand Theatre]] in [[Atlanta|Atlanta, Georgia]], United States. *[[1941]] &ndash; [[The Holocaust in Ukraine]]: [[Nazi Germany|German]] troops murder over 15,000 Jews at [[Drobytsky Yar]], a ravine southeast of the city of [[Kharkiv]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; World War II: The [[Battle of Mount Austen, the Galloping Horse, and the Sea Horse]] begins during the [[Guadalcanal Campaign]]. *[[1943]] &ndash; World War II: The [[Battle of Arawe]] begins during the [[New Britain campaign]]. *[[1945]] &ndash; [[Occupation of Japan]]/[[Shinto Directive]]: General [[Douglas MacArthur]] orders that [[Shinto]] be abolished as the state religion of Japan. *[[1960]] &ndash; [[Richard Paul Pavlick|Richard Pavlick]] is arrested for plotting to assassinate [[President-elect of the United