{{Infobox website | name = Tor Carding Forum | logo = Tor Carding Forums logo.png | logo_size = | logocaption = | screenshot = | caption = | collapsible = | collapsetext = | url = | commercial = | type = [[Internet forum]] | registration = | language = [[English language|English]] | num_users = | content_license = | owner = | author = | editor = | launch_date = | revenue = | alexa = | current_status = Offline | footnotes = }}
The '''Tor Carding Forum''' (TCF) was a [[Tor (anonymity network)|Tor]]-based [[Internet forum|forum]] specializing in the trade of [[Carding (fraud)|stolen credit card]] details, [[identity theft]] and [[Counterfeit money|currency counterfeiting]]. The site was founded by an individual known as 'Verto' who also founded the now defunct [[Evolution (marketplace)|Evolution]] [[darknet market]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wired Staff|title=The Most Dangerous People on the Internet Right Now|url=https://www.wired.com/2015/01/dangerous-people-internet-right-now/|accessdate=1 August 2015|date=1 January 2015}}</ref>
The site required $50 for registration.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kiell|title=A Carder’s First Experience|url=https://www.deepdotweb.com/2014/12/11/a-carders-first-experience/|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=11 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Greenberg|first1=Andy|title=The Dark Web Gets Darker With Rise of the ‘Evolution’ Drug Market|url=https://www.wired.com/2014/09/dark-web-evolution/|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=18 September 2014}}</ref>
A 2013 investigation into counterfeit banknotes in [[Pittsburgh]] led to a source of [[Uganda]]n fakes being identified as having been purchased via the Tor Carding Forums.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rohrlich|first1=Justin|title=The Counterfeiting Missionary and the Fake Pittsburgh Playboy|url=https://news.vice.com/article/the-counterfeiting-missionary-and-the-fake-pittsburgh-playboy|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=27 January 2015}}</ref> By December 2014 Ryan Andrew Gustafson a.k.a. "Jack Farrel" and "Willy Clock", a US citizen living in Uganda was arrested for large scale sale of counterfeit [[Counterfeit United States currency|United States currency]] by the [[U.S. Secret Service]] which was being sold through the Tor Carding Forums as well as other [[crime forum]]s.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Krebs|first1=Brian|title=Alleged Counterfeiter "Willy Clock" Arrested|url=http://krebsonsecurity.com/2014/12/alleged-counterfeiter-willy-clock-arrested/|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=December 2014}}</ref>
In December 2014 the site closed following a hack, directing users to Evolution's forums.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Farivar|first1=Cyrus|title=After Silk Road takedowns, Dark Web drug sites still thriving|url=https://arstechnica.com/business/2014/12/after-two-silk-road-takedowns-dark-web-drug-sites-still-thriving/|accessdate=1 August 2015|date=19 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=DeepDotWeb|title=Evolution Marketplace Staff Speak: We are growing fast!|url=https://www.deepdotweb.com/2014/05/10/evolution-marketplace-staff-speak-we-are-growing-fast/|accessdate=16 August 2015|date=10 May 2014}}</ref>
In June 2015 a [[dark web]] researcher identified the [[clearnet (networking)|clearnet]] IP address of a similar hidden service branded 'The Tor Carding Forum V2'<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cox|first1=Joseph|title=This Researcher Is Hunting Down IP Addresses of Dark Web Sites|url=http://motherboard.vice.com/read/this-researcher-is-hunting-down-ip-addresses-of-dark-web-sites|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=22 June 2015}}</ref> which was subsequently shut down.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Guthrie Weissman|first1=Cale|title=The dark web is growing but people have already figured out how to track down its most hidden websites|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/dark-web-researcher-discovers-ip-addresses-in-plain-sight-2015-6?r=US&IR=T|accessdate=8 December 2015|date=23 June 2015}}</ref> == References == {{reflist}} {{Tor hidden services}} [[Category:Internet forums]] [[Category:Cybercrime]] [[Category:Defunct Tor hidden services|Carding]] [[Category:Crime forums]] [[Category:Carding (fraud)]] {{crime-stub}} {{Internet-stub}}
